This paper presents a method for improving instance segmentation performance using existing instance mask annotations and data augmentation techniques. The method involves exploiting pixel redundancy in the background and using a location probability map to guide object placement. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning, suggesting that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a model to improve performance, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of data augmentation techniques and the focus on improving model performance also suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the use of a probability map to guide object placement suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category, as this technique is commonly used in robotics applications.
